OL,3,CFirearms officer tells inquest he had
OL,4,C'no choice' but to shoot knifeman
OL,6,FOfficer A told the jury: 'He was
OL,7,Fclosing me down ` I was backpedalling.
OL,8,FI knew that negotiation, which would
OL,9,Fhave been my priority, was not working.
OL,11,F'We failed with the other less lethal
OL,12,Foptions. I felt I was left with no
OL,13,Fchoice.
OL,15,F'It was the most dynamic and quick
OL,16,Fpolice incident I have been involved
OL,17,Fin. I have not been involved in
OL,18,Fanything that has happened as fast as
OL,19,Fthat.'
