OL,3,CFirearms officer tells inquest he had
OL,4,C'no choice' but to shoot knifeman
OL,6,F'My immediate concern, not knowing
OL,7,Fwhat had happened previously, was that
OL,8,Fhe was approaching those officers to
OL,9,Fpotentially do harm. I had to do
OL,10,Fsomething to mitigate that risk to
OL,11,Fthose officers.'
OL,13,FThe officer said there was no time to
OL,14,Fspeak to Officer B about their plan
OL,15,Fwhen they arrived in the car park.
OL,17,FOfficer A said 'He started walking
OL,18,Ftowards me. I raised my weapon and
OL,19,Faimed at him at that point and shouted
OL,20,Fanother command for him to drop the
OL,21,Fknife.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/11
