OL,3,CFirearms officer tells inquest he had
OL,4,C'no choice' but to shoot knifeman
OL,6,F'He walked through the smoke of the
OL,7,Fstun grenade, there was no stopping
OL,8,Fwhen that stun grenade went off.
OL,10,F'The fact he's walking towards me and
OL,11,Fclosing that gap means the risk could
OL,12,Fbe high.'
OL,14,FOfficer A recalled Officer B having a
OL,15,Fbaton gun, which he heard go off but
OL,16,F'did not achieve its aim'.
OL,18,FThe jury was told that officers had
OL,19,Falso used Tasers which were
OL,20,Funsuccessful in disarming Mr Ciolac
OL,21,Fbefore he 'sprinted' at Officer A.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/11
