OL,3,CFirearms officer tells inquest he had
OL,4,C'no choice' but to shoot knifeman
OL,6,FThe officer said the default tactic
OL,7,Fwhen someone had a knife in a public
OL,8,Farea was to 'challenge from a position
OL,9,Fof cover.'
OL,11,FOfficer A told Ms Kaushal he had never
OL,12,Ffired the gun, which was a carbine,
OL,13,Foutside his firearms training.
OL,15,FHe said: 'Outside of training I never
OL,16,Ffired the weapon live. I would have
OL,17,Fthe carbine on me, potentially I would
OL,18,Fhave pointed it at people, but prior
OL,19,Fto this job I never fired this weapon.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/11
