OL,3,CFirearms officer tells inquest he had
OL,4,C'no choice' but to shoot knifeman
OL,6,FOfficer A replied: 'We do routinely
OL,7,Fshout 'armed police' when we arrive
OL,8,Fbut it is not a training standard. We
OL,9,Fdo what we think we need to do at the
OL,10,Ftime.'
OL,12,FA pathologist previously told the
OL,13,Finquest Mr Ciolac's cause of death was
OL,14,Fa gunshot wound to the abdomen and
OL,15,Fthere was 'no evidence' to suggest he
OL,16,Fwas under the influence of drugs or
OL,17,Falcohol at the time of his death.
OL,19,FThe inquest continues.
